看来大家对内存相关的比较感兴趣，本期再为大家说一下，Chromium团队“大概”是怎么做的。


`一、History`
>   1.As of 2015 June, memory reduction was raised as one of the priorities of the web-platform team  
>   2.At that point, no one knew even what percentage of renderer’s memory is consumed by Blink  
>   3.Since then, we’ve been working on understanding Blink’s memory and identifying sweet spots to reduce it

降低内存占用被提上日程之时，他们对内存的情况也是模糊的，只知道“很高”，不知道到底有多高？百分比是多少？哪里是”内存大户“？

`二、Strategy`
>   1.Tooling  
>   2.Understanding  
>   3.Reducing  

符合大谷歌的风格，先整工具！这里主要依靠Memory-Infra和Telemetry。

Blink中混合使用了4个内存分配器，祭出Memory-Infra，负责记录详细信息。Telemetry是个性能测试框架，负责运行用例，收集性能信息。
>   1.PartitionAlloc  
>   2.Oilpan  
>   3.tcmalloc  
>   4.system allocator  

这次顺手清理了tcmalloc和system allocator，Memory-Infra收集剩下的PartitionAlloc和Oilpan内存分配信息。这样Renderer中Blink的内存就被分解，细化了，找出到底是谁占用的内存多。

工具化，用数据说话，才是正道！那些想当然的优化，总是被现实击的粉粉碎，只会得到然并卵的结果！

![](data:image/png;base64,)


分解Renderer内存
```Renderer = V8 + PartitionAlloc + Oilpan + Skia + …```

分解PartitionAlloc分配的内存
```PartitionAlloc = Buffer + FastMalloc + Node + Layout```
  
继续
```Buffer = StringImpl + Vector + HashTable + …```
>   The largest consumer is the Buffer partition  
>   StringImpls, Vectors, HashTables, ArrayBuffers etc

```FastMalloc = SharedBuffer + ...```
>   The second largest consumer is the FastMalloc partitio  
>   SharedBuffers, all DOM objects except for Nodes and LayoutObjects

就这样找出了内存占用的Sweet Spots.

`三、如何接入Memory Infra系统呢？`
>  1.Create a base::trace_event::MemoryDumpProvider for your component.  
>  2.Register/Unregister your base::trace_event::MemoryDumpProvider with the base::trace_event::MemoryDumpManager.

一般是资源管理类，继承base::trace_event::MemoryDumpProvider接口，实现OnMemoryDump方法，再将自己注册到MemoryDumpManager中去，退出时，再反注册。
注册
```
  // Each process uses a singleton MemoryDumpManager
  base::trace_event::MemoryDumpManager::GetInstance()->RegisterDumpProvider(
  my_memory_dump_provider_, my_single_thread_task_runner_);
```

统计信息
```
bool MyComponent::OnMemoryDump(
    const base::trace_event::MemoryDumpArgs& args,
    base::trace_event::ProcessMemoryDump* process_memory_dump) {
  for (const auto& allocation : my_allocations_) {
    auto* dump = process_memory_dump->CreateAllocatorDump(
        "path/to/my/component/allocation_" + allocation.id().ToString());
    dump->AddScalar(base::trace_event::MemoryAllocatorDump::kNameSize,
                    base::trace_event::MemoryAllocatorDump::kUnitsBytes,
                    allocation.size_bytes());
  // While you will typically have a kNameSize entry, you can add additional
  // entries to your dump with free-form names. In this example we also dump
  // an object's "free_size", assuming the object may not be entirely in use.
  dump->AddScalar("free_size",
                  base::trace_event::MemoryAllocatorDump::kUnitsBytes,
                  allocation.free_size_bytes());
  }
}
```

反注册
```
...
  // Each process uses a singleton MemoryDumpManager
  base::trace_event::MemoryDumpManager::GetInstance()->UnregisterDumpProvider(
      my_memory_dump_provider_);
...
```

已接入的模块

- Discardable Memory Tracks usage of discardable memory throughout chrome.
- GPU tracks GL and other GPU object allocations.
- V8 tracks heap size for JS.
- many more....

打开这个Flag:--enable-heap-profiling，然后看下面动画~
![](data:image/gif;base64,)
动画中，使用的当前UC版本，信息较少，Chrome最新版，信息要丰富许多了。但是信息太多了，发现Tracing时，不能录制时间过长，不然结束时很容易解析失败，而且UC的Tracing页面相对比较容易崩溃。
